@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About | David Buckley</PageTitle>

<MudGrid>
    <MudItem xs="12" md="4">
        <MudCard Elevation="3" Class="text-center pa-4">
            <MudAvatar Style="width:150px;height:150px;margin:0 auto 16px;" Color="Color.Primary">
                <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Person" Style="font-size:100px;" />
            </MudAvatar>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="fw-bold">David Buckley</MudText>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Color="Color.Secondary">Senior Software Engineer &amp; AI Developer</MudText>
            <MudDivider Class="my-4" />
            <MudStack Spacing="2">
                <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center">
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Work" Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Small" />
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">30+ Years Experience</MudText>
                </MudStack>
                <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center">
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.LocationOn" Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Small" />
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">United Kingdom</MudText>
                </MudStack>
                <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center">
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Psychology" Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Small" />
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">AI &amp; Security Specialist</MudText>
                </MudStack>
                <MudStack Row="true" AlignItems="AlignItems.Center">
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Email" Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Small" />
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Available for Opportunities</MudText>
                </MudStack>
            </MudStack>
            <MudDivider Class="my-4" />
            <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary" FullWidth="true" Href="/contact">
                Get In Touch
            </MudButton>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>

    <MudItem xs="12" md="8">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" Class="mb-4 fw-bold">About Me</MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            I have been writing software professionally since 1994 and I still find it genuinely exciting.
            Over three decades I have worked across desktop, web, mobile and cloud, but the last few years
            have pulled me strongly toward two things that I think are shaping where software goes next:
            artificial intelligence and application security.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            On the AI side I build real production systems rather than proof of concept toys. I use Semantic
            Kernel and Azure OpenAI to add intelligent features to .NET applications, things like AI chat
            assistants, document summarisation, anomaly detection and smart search. I care about making AI
            reliable and auditable because most of my work touches sectors like healthcare where a wrong
            answer is not just annoying, it can cause harm.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            Security has been a growing focus for the same reason. Working on patient data systems forces
            you to treat security as a first class concern rather than something you bolt on at the end.
            I apply OWASP principles, model threats during design, and push for penetration testing before
            go live rather than hoping nothing breaks. That mindset has saved real projects from real problems.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-6">
            The foundation under all of this is the .NET ecosystem. C#, ASP.NET Core, Blazor, Entity Framework
            Core, and .NET MAUI are the tools I reach for every day. I am on .NET 10 and I follow the platform
            closely because knowing what is coming lets me make better architectural decisions now.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-3 fw-bold">Career Highlights</MudText>
        <MudTimeline>
            <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Medium">
                <ItemContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">AI Engineering and Security Focus</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Color="Color.Secondary">2022 to Present</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        Shipping AI powered features into production .NET applications using Semantic Kernel,
                        Azure OpenAI and RAG pipelines. Embedding security practices into every project from
                        threat modelling and OWASP reviews to penetration testing and identity hardening.
                        Delivering BookIt, Curo, Patient CRM and an AI diagnostic assistant.
                    </MudText>
                </ItemContent>
            </MudTimelineItem>
            <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Secondary" Size="Size.Medium">
                <ItemContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Modern .NET and Cloud</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Color="Color.Secondary">2016 to 2022</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        Deep dive into ASP.NET Core, Azure and microservices. Designed REST APIs and event
                        driven architectures for enterprise clients. Started applying formal security reviews
                        after a client security audit showed gaps that mattered.
                    </MudText>
                </ItemContent>
            </MudTimelineItem>
            <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Tertiary" Size="Size.Medium">
                <ItemContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Enterprise .NET Development</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Color="Color.Secondary">2005 to 2016</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        Senior developer across finance, retail and healthcare. WinForms, WPF, ASP.NET Web
                        Forms, early MVC, SQL Server design and optimisation. This era taught me the importance
                        of maintainable code because I was the one maintaining it five years later.
                    </MudText>
                </ItemContent>
            </MudTimelineItem>
            <MudTimelineItem Color="Color.Warning" Size="Size.Medium">
                <ItemContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Early Career</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Color="Color.Secondary">1994 to 2005</MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                        Started with Visual Basic and early .NET Framework. Built desktop and database
                        systems across several industries. Writing code for actual users from the very
                        beginning shaped how I think about software even now.
                    </MudText>
                </ItemContent>
            </MudTimelineItem>
        </MudTimeline>
    </MudItem>
</MudGrid>
